ilippines' first Olympic double gold medalist.\", \"from\": 948, \"to\": 1114, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1066, \"end\": 1077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9999982385360962, \"rank\": 1.7614651331734578e-06, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His pair of historic performances allowed the country to win multiple golds in a single Olympics for the first time as the Philippines tied for 37th place in the medal tally - its highest ranking in exactly six decades.\", \"from\": 1116, \"to\": 1335, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1239, \"end\": 1250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9999982385360962, \"rank\": 1.7614651331734578e-06, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Villegas, meanwhile, made the most of her Olympic debut, snaggingbronzein the women's 50kg division.\", \"from\": 1337, \"to\": 1437, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Philippines' other bronze medalist, boxerNesthy Petecio, served as flag bearer in the opening ceremony alongside teammate Carlo Paalam.\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1443, \"end\": 1454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9999982385360962, \"rank\": 1.7614651331734578e-06, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}, {\"begin\": 1565, \"end\": 1577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlo_Paalam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlo Paalam\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlo_Paalam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http: